# Project Goals

## Main Goal

The goal of this project is to document the planning, development, and progress of LB, my personal Claude-powered automation bot.

LB is intended to become a personal AI assistant that saves time, filters information, supports decision-making, and helps automate repetitive tasks across different parts of my life.

As the project grows, LB should be built with safe handling of accounts, permissions, API keys, and personal data in mind.

## Core Goals

- Build a personal automation bot centered around Claude
- Create a system that can connect to useful apps and services
- Reduce the amount of manual checking I have to do every day
- Filter noisy information into clear, useful alerts
- Help me make faster and better decisions
- Keep human approval involved for important actions
- Document the full build process in GitHub
- Use this project as a long-term portfolio piece

## Personal Use Goals

LB should eventually help with:

- Resale alerts and eBay comp research
- Trading research and market/news filtering
- Reading and summarizing emails
- Calendar and scheduling support
- Setting weekly tee times
- Daily reminders and task organization
- Tracking personal projects
- Finding useful information quickly
- Sending alerts when something actually matters

## Reliability and Security Goals

LB should be built in a way that is reliable, organized, and safe to expand over time.

As the project grows, I want to focus on:

- Keeping API keys and tokens out of GitHub
- Using environment variables for sensitive information
- Limiting each integration to only the access it actually needs
- Tracking errors clearly so problems can be reviewed later
- Keeping logs organized and useful
- Documenting setup steps and changes
- Building the project in a way that can be tested and improved over time

## Decision Support Goal

LB is not meant to blindly make major decisions on its own.

The goal is for LB to gather information, filter noise, summarize what matters, and give clear recommendations so I can make the final decision.

## GitHub Goal

This repository is meant to show the full process of building LB from the ground up.
